    public interface LeafEvent
extends BuckEvent
    LeafEvents represent events that have no logical children and are useful for tracking the time buck is spending logically grouped by categories, such as Parse, Javac, or Dx. An example of something that wouldn't be a good candidate for a LeafEvent would be a RuleEvent since we're not spending an appreciable amount of time in the rules but in the steps instead.
